Title: Object: Santa Maria Gratiosa
Description: The Rest on the Flight into Egypt, with the Virgin suckling the Child seated beneath a tree, while St Joseph looks on; after Bernardino Passeri. 1588 Engraving
Curator's comments: For a complete list of Graffico's known works see E. Lincoln, 'The studio inventory of Camillo Graffico, engraver and fountaineer', PQ, vol.xxix, 2012, pp.259-80. This print is number 12 in the list. In a later state of 1597, Graffico's address is replaced by that of Cesare Capranica.
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Sir Hans Sloane (with Philipe's large pencilled HS)
